Regulatory & Government Affairs: 19 local exchange carriers'
(LECs') proposal to rebalance their rates

          The Nebraska Public Service Commission will hear oral
arguments Jan. 8 on a motion by commission staff members to
"bifurcate" a proceeding on 19 local exchange carriers' (LECs')
proposal to rebalance their rates.  The companies proposed to add
a $2 subscriber line charge to customers' monthly bills and to
reduce access charges by $19 million annually.  M. Gene Hand, PSC
Director-communications, said the staff considers the proposed
change as a local rate increase, since it would not apply to all
LECs in the state.  In a separate proceeding, the PSC plans to
hold hearings around the state Jan. 29-Feb. 8 on a proposed
"consumer bill of rights" for the competitive local exchange
market...



