a winning bid of $16 million for a cellular license in Madhya
Pradesh, the largest state in India.  A new company, Cellular
Communication India Ltd. will be formed, with AirTouch owning a
49% share.  Service on the company's network, which will use the
GSM (Global System for Mobile Communications) digital technology
standard, is expected to begin in the third quarter of this
year...



