-FINANCIAL AND CORPORATE:LG TAKES STAKE IN DACOM

TWW-2 January 1996-FINANCIAL AND CORPORATE:LG TAKES
STAKE IN DACOM
TELECOMWORLDWIRE--(C) 1995 M2 COMMUNICATIONS LTD

LG Group, one of South Korea's largest conglomerate
companies, has taken a controlling stake in DACOM,
the South Korean domestic telecommunications company. 
The move marks an end to an active battle between
local firms for control of the company, which is the
largest competitor to Korea Telecom.




<A HREF ="#HeadList">Back to Headline List</A><BR>
