-FINANCIAL AND CORPORATE:PARTNER IN SIGHT FOR
ENERGIS?

TWW-2 January 1996-FINANCIAL AND CORPORATE:PARTNER IN
SIGHT FOR ENERGIS?
TELECOMWORLDWIRE--(C) 1995 M2 COMMUNICATIONS LTD

ENERGIS, the British loss-making telecommunications
subsidiary of the National Grid is said to be
considering strategic alliances and joint ventures in
a bid to improve its fortune.  Some sources suggest
that IBM Global Network is considering forming the
alliance. In the past 18 months Energis has lost over
GBP93m.




