January 12, 1996

INDIA - INTERNATIONAL CARRIER TO EXTEND INTERNET
ACCESS

Videsh Sanchar Nigam Ltd (VSNL), India's international telephone
monopoly, will install 12 more Internet nodes in regional capitals to
extend access to the Internet. Presently, VSNL has one Internet
node in each of Bangalore, Pune, Bombay, Calcutta, Delhi and
Madras.

The director of VSNL, Amitabh Kumar, said that the VSNL had
already begun providing leased line services, including 64 kbps
connectivity through wireless radio links. According to Kumar there
are 2000 Internet connections presently in India. This number is
expected to rise to 10,000 by the end of 1996.



