UNITED STATES APPROVES SAS/UNITED AIRLINES ALLIANCE

from TRANSPORT EUROPE, 15 November 1996, No. 67

The United States Department of Transportation approved, on November 5, a
cooperation alliance between SAS, the Scandinavian airline, and UNITED
AIRLINES of the US. The Department also granted anti-trust immunity to the
three-way SAS-United-LUFTHANSA alliance as part of the open sky Agreement
signed by the US and Germany last Spring. SAS and United Airlines, which
signed a cooperation accord in September 1995, have been jointly offering
66 "code-sharing" transatlantic flights since April.

